<HEAD>POSTSCRIPT.</HEAD>
<P>SINCE the foregoing di&s;cour&s;e, were &s;ent to the pre&s;s, &s;ome things remarkable have occurred, that, by the ble&s;&s;ing of God, may awaken and alarm the country. Particularly the late infernal plot of the infamous <HI>Arnold</HI> for delivering up our truly worthy General, and the Army and important works at We&s;t Point, into the hands of the enemy; whereby they might &s;oon open a pa&s;&s;age from New-York to Albany, and thence to Canada. Here was trea&s;on, cur&s;ed trea&s;on, and wickedne&s;s that wants a name, perhaps in hell as well as earth. And altho' heaven has, in a very won|derful way, di&s;covered and broke the &s;nare, ble&s;&s;ed be God forever and ever, yet all the mi&s;chievous de&s;igns connected with the horrid plan are not ended. The late extraordinary movements and exertions of the Northern enemy. The taking, as we hear, of Fort-Ann, Fort William Henry, or Fort George and Fort Edward, burn|ing and plundering the towns and &s;ettlements in tho&s;e parts, and on Mohawk river, and killing and captivating the poor inhabitants, together with the de&s;olations com|mitted at Royalton, were mo&s;t probably concerted in the afore&s;aid infernal plot. Surely we cannot now he&s;itate a moment longer, whether it be not ab&s;olutely ne|ce&s;&s;ary to awake and look about our&s;elves, in good earne&s;t. We are, e&s;pecially on the&s;e long extended frontiers, and through the <HI>Grants,</HI> in jeopardy every hour. Every thing we hold dear and &s;acred, is eminently expo&s;ed to the ravages of a Ty|rant's me cenaries and &s;avage cut throats! The dagger is at our brea&s;ts, and the tomahawk over our heads! And the &s;ituation of our whole country and our army is truly alarming.&mdash;My dear countrymen, what think you of the&s;e things?&mdash;Shall we after the mo&s;t glorious &s;truggle for our liberties and our all, that ever the world behold, &s;ink down in a fatal lethargy, let the enemy take ALL, and en&s;lave me and our children forever? Why &s;hould any call his hou&s;es lands, money or pro|vi&s;ions his own, at &s;uch a time as this? Is it not high time that every one &s;hould be ready to part with all, except for nece&s;&s;ary &s;ub&s;i&s;tence, for the &s;upport of his country's cau&s;e? Then we &s;hould &s;oon &s;ee a very happy turn in our affairs We &s;hould have <HI>an Army</HI> and have i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> well furni&s;hed and &s;upported. God has gives us ability&punc; And could we u&s;e our vigorous ex<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters">ions for a little time, with a common ble&s;&s;ing we might rea&s;onably hope to &s;ecure our independence and with it every privilege. <HI>The Lo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">d is a man of war,</HI> and he is on the &s;ide of Liberty, of the ju&s;t rights of mankind&punc; Implore his help, and put your tru&s;t in him. And, MAY heaven in&s;pire every man with a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> and intrepidity in this glorious cau&s;e, and read forth our armies to victory, glory, and renown. AMEN.</P>
